titleInfo.title: USA v. Andretti
titleInfo.subTitle: JUDGMENT for Revocation of Supervised Release as to Anthony J. Andretti (1). Defendant admitted guilt to violation of the Mandatory Condition of the term of supervision and is committed to the custody of the Bureau of Prisons for a term of 15 months, to be served consecutively to the time imposed in state court; 45 months supervised release with special conditions; $50 special assessment has been paid; $14,954.92 restitution remains due and payable, as to defendant Anthony J. Andretti. Ordered by Judge Laurie Smith Camp. (4 Certified copies to USM)(JAE, )

titleInfo.title: USA v. Andretti
titleInfo.subTitle: ORDER as to defendant Anthony J. Andretti. A final dispositional hearing will be held before Chief Judge Laurie Smith Camp in Courtroom No. 2, Third Floor, Roman L. Hruska U.S. Courthouse, 111 South 18th Plaza, Omaha, Nebraska, at 10:30 a.m. on February 14, 2013. Defendant must be present in person. Defendant Anthony Andretti is committed to the custody of the Attorney General or his designated representative for confinement in a correctional facility. Defendant shall be afforded a reasonable opportunity for private consultation with defense counsel. Upon order of a United States court or upon request of an attorney for the government, the person in charge of the corrections facility shall deliver defendant to the United States Marshal for the purpose of an appearance in connection with a court proceeding. Ordered by Magistrate Judge Thomas D. Thalken. (GJG)
